@page "/about/game-objects"

<h1>About Game Objects</h1>

<div class="container">
    <div>
        <h2>Colony</h2>
        <p>
            A colony has several stats that change via events during gameplay.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-group">
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Population</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    Represents the amount of citizens living in your colony.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Approval</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    A percentage rating of how your citizens judge your decisions and leadership.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Wealth</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    A measure of the colony's economic success.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Tech</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    An abstract rating of a colony's technological and scientific output.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Industry</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    A measure of the colony's manufacturing and production capabilities.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <div>
        <h2>Planet Type</h2>
        <p>
            Planet types signify the major climatological characteristics of planets.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-group">
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Name</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    Give each planet type a unique name to add flavor to your games.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Temperature Rating</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    Represents a long-term average surface temperature for the planet.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h4 class="card-header">Land Cover</h4>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    A percentage indicating the amount of land on the planet that is above sea level.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <div>
        <h2>Event Effect</h2>
        <p>
            An event effect represents a single outcome of an event that causes changes in each of a colony's stats.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <h4 class="card-header">Example</h4>
        <div class="card-body">
            <p>
                Using the "PAWTI" order, an event's effects are shown in a compact form of -/-/-/-/-.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    10/-5/5/0/0
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <div>
        <h2>World Event</h2>
        <p>
            World events have a 'Name' and 'Description' property to give context to the singular event effect that is tied to it.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <h4 class="card-header">Example</h4>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h6 class="card-title">Tectonic Havoc</h6>
            <p>
                A string of earthquakes has hit several highly populated areas in the colony. 
                Restoration efforts have drained many of the colony's resources.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    0/0/-15/-10/-10
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <div>
        <h2>Decision Event</h2>
        <p>
            Decision events, with 'Name' and 'Description' properties analagous to those of World Events, offer a choice between to options that resolves to a single event effect on a colony.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <h4 class="card-header">Example</h4>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h6 class="card-title">Between a rock and a hard place...</h6>
            <p>
                Recent surveys of a beloved historic mountain range have revealed an untapped trove of raw materials just under the surface. 
                Mining and fracking within these sites would yield high ROIs for the colony's industries, 
                however the local residents are adamantly opposed to cutting out the cultural heart of their lands. 
                Leaving the mountains untouched would likely improve your administration's approval rating.
            </p>
            <h8 class="card-subtitle">Option A</h8>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    0/-20/30/0/25
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h8 class="card-subtitle">Option B</h8>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                <li class="list-group-item">
                    0/20/0/0/0
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>